alert.note: Alert for Coastal Dixie (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Coastal Flood Warning issued January 15 at 3:28PM EST until January 16 at 7:00PM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 7 PM THIS EVENING TO 7 PM EST SUNDAY... * WHAT...Minor to moderate coastal flooding possible with water levels 2 to 4 feet above normally dry ground around the time of high tide. * WHERE...Coastal Dixie County. * WHEN...From 7 PM this evening to 7 PM EST Sunday. * IMPACTS...Water levels will begin rising this evening. Flooding of areas along the coast in Horseshoe Beach and Suwannee are possible. Water overtopping seawalls, impacting roads and non- elevated structures is possible.
info.instruction: Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property. If travel is required, do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth.
